content.detailedDescription:
I walkded out of my buildings to the front porched for a smoke break, was prob 730-745 pm saturday the 12th 2013. it was already dark and the street im on has a couple of street lights out so you could see the sky little more clear than normally at night. i was smoking and just kinda spacing out looking up and i noticed an object coming from the south west. i figured was a plane because pdx is south east of my location, maybe ten or so miles away. generally the air traffic travels oppsite path that the object was traveling so i watched it about 3-4 mins come from the south east over the top of the buildin and continue in north east direction. it did fairly close but the  camera on my iphone like usual was being useless and had tough time keeping hand steady, fortunatly after it passed over head and was maybe a couple hundred feet away i was able to get a decent shot. it moved like how a car moves on ice, like there was no wind resistance slowin it down or drag. it made no noise and was solid object, didnt flicker or morph in any way. after passing over head it slowly blended in with sky and that was that. august 2007 
i was watering front lawn about 5pm, it was sunny and clear day when boat shaped solid black craft was crusing about 500 ft off the ground maybe doing 100 mph, if that. it was one of those things after its gone you start looking all around you hoping that someone else saw it, so unfortunatly after witnessing that this doesnt compare
content.summary: A gliding boat/triangle shaped craft, assuming it was black but impossible to know, had white lights in the back

content.detailedDescription: I was flying to california from illinois when i looked out the window. here i see this massive egg-shaped object flying by the plane. i took pictures of it and then a video when the object changed direction. it started flying away from the plane so eventually it just went out of sight.
content.summary: Large egg-like object spotted while i was on a plane

content.detailedDescription: I was standing outside when i seen a fireball in the sky so i ran inside the house to grab my iphone and i came back out and took photos of this object as it was flying away from me at a steady rate. to my surprise there was another object over my house and i took photos of that one as it was flying away from me. i have the photos!!!
content.summary: Seen fire ball and i have 10 photos of object

content.detailedDescription: I was taking my dog outside to go to the bathroom in the yard before putting her to bed at 11 pm. i always scan the yard and sky when outside.  i noticed  a large number of sparkling orange lights in the sky and thought they were fireworks, but they did not fall to the ground as fireworks do.  they made no sound. they traveled in a southeasterly direction. i watched them until they disappeared behind the trees. i was very excited and watched them as long as i could see them. they were flying east of the fairgrounds. the lights did not form a pattern and did not act like fireworks.
content.summary: I saw a fleet of orange lights traveling in southeasterly direction over town. at first i thought they were fireworks but they didn't fall to ground just traveled straight across my visible sky.

content.detailedDescription: Went out to check the mail, saw a star like object just before moonrise.  went back after dusk to dark with bino's.   object flashed, changed colors, changed shapes, and got brighter then dimmer, then brighter and was moving slowly toward the west.  upon binoc's siting, object had a electrical storm, very changing light patterns and lightning.  it had it's own flying dark rocks, and changed from a circle to a large flat glowing bar.  at times it looked like a fingerprint.  some objects appeared to be entering and exiting or flying around it.  a large wedge shaped dark place was flying near, under then past then back by it.  i could not see the dark plane in the binoc's.  there was a large orange planet following it underneath very slowly.  i felt exilerated and  amazed at it.   it was very cold and i had to go inside
content.summary: Looked like a star at first, gave off quite a light show, and changed shapes, and colors

content.detailedDescription: I was in my front yard, my father n law was buffing out the top side of his r.V. and he wanted me to take a look at it. as i was looking up at the side of the r.V. something caught my eye. at first i thought it was a balloon but it changed direction as we were observing it. after several minutes i told my father n law i want to try and video tape it. i went in the house got my video camera i then tried to find a video tape i could use. all that took about 4 to 5 minutes i came back outside and began to record. i first noticed the object moving slowly south west of me then it would come back north west it did that for about 10 minutes. some times it would stop in one spot. as you hear me say in the video it was fading in and out i thought it was going behind clouds but it was a clear afternoon the object was fading in and out and tilting side to side. there were several trees on both side of where i was recording so im sure they can be used as some type of reference. not until i viewed the tape later did i notice there was a second object it was silver and gave off a bright reflection but the sun was setting behind it the sliver object was at 1oclock of the object i was recording.  i lost sight as my video camera didn't have a very good zoom on it. i really didn't have any feelings i just wondered what i was seeing. i was there with my mother n law and my father n law he is a minister. i have had this for many years i have only shown it to 3 or 4 people but i have many questions and i am reaching out to you  hoping with the technology you have you can maybe give me insight to what i was recording that day.
content.summary: After viewing the tape there are 2 one white and one silver

content.detailedDescription:
Had just bought a new camera and was outside taking quick pix of a passing coal train.  i live on the western slopes of colorado along rt. 92 about 6 miles east of delta.  the western slopes of the grand mesa are in the background.  also in all 3 pix there is a jet above the object which barely moves, so it gives an idea as to how quickly the pix were being taken.  (time stamps on the pix is 4:23, 4:24, & 4:24 pm)  i didn't notice the object until i downloaded the pictures onto my computer.  that's when i saw the object in only the 1st pix.  the object only appears in the first picture above one of the coal-cars in the train.  in the picture the object looks like a cross between a tear-drop and an oval shape and appears to be black with a smooth surface.  antelope hill is in the lower background with the grand mesa beyond and above that feature.  first thought after seeing this is that it's a ufo!  this is now the 6th ufo i've seen in the skies out here (this is a desert area not far from the border of utah).
i did not see this in real-time, only saw it after i looked at the pictures on my computer.  at the time i was looking into the view window of the camera and not paying attention to what was happening.  plus it must have been moving quite quickly to only appear in the one picture.
content.summary: Series of 3 pix within 15 seconds object in first pix

content.detailedDescription:
At 19:20 hours on 19 october 2013, as i was leaving my home, i sighted a large, very bright white light hovering above the southern edge of my property in the voc of sedona, az. 

i took about 5-6 photos with my cell phone but only two photos were any good as once again my camera began; as during one other sighting this month while photographing another ufo, the camera controls began flickering wildly and again refused to photograph correctly.

i did not have the time to grab another camera as i had to leave being my wife was getting off work and was waiting in uptown for me to pick her up. fortunately, the object stayed nearby where i first sighted it and/or moved nearby the sedona airport and was visible all the time while we were on our return trip to the village of oak creek. my wife and numerous others also sighted the object (as well as the quite large full moon which was off to the eastern part of the sky).

the object, upon our return to the voc, was further south of the location where i first had sighted it; but i did not see it leave or am aware as to the length of time it was viewable. i am sure a great many others were viewing the object/craft as numerous cars were parked alongside the roadway and appeared to be watching the object!
content.summary: Again, as on another evening during october i sighted and photographed a large boomerang hovering above my home in voc sedona, az

content.detailedDescription: I was asleep inside home, had several layers of clothing on as it was very cold. home was being remodeled. only heat was kerosene heater. asleep on two couches pushed together in living room. a "pit" couch without middle causing a large playpen like bed. awoke outside in the snow to a very loud sound like a train, was naked and was locked out of the home deadbolts were still locked from the inside. beat on the door until boyfriend finally awoke and let me in. only other door/exit was about 6 foot off the ground. no stairs. have no idea how i got outside, how i became undressed, clothing missing all together and never found. kept this to myself for years, now need to know what happened.Was not on drugs, did not drink, started having panic attacks after this experience. completely serious not a hoax please help. can't go to psychiatrist tell this story and expect to walk out. have reoccurring dreams and strange dreams of other worldly things. memory of event is starting to become vague. have lupus and other health issues affecting my memory. want to know what happened, need help.Also had a scar that wasn't there before over left ovary and 3 dots in form of triangle on abdomen.
content.summary: Think i was taken need help to remember

content.detailedDescription:
I was standing in my yard after the fire truck's left from a house fire across the street. as they were leaving , we noticed what appeared to be a long white cylinder with a black ring around one area of this. it was falling from the sky a little fast but, not too fast. it had a dome on one end that also had the same color light on the inside of it & it was round shaped. the first thing i thought of was, it's a ufo ! i have seen this very same object 2 day's before this happened. 
                there was no sound at all. we could actually see the redish tint all around the object. as i recorded it, it started falling from the south going to the south west area & then it was gone.
               i was amazed at what we saw but, i also knew it wasn't right. in my opinion, i knew it was a ufo ! no sound at all, no wing's, and the fact that it had a dome on it was really out of place . it didn't leave any trail of smoke at all. totally silent.

                 while i was recording, i watched it go behind the tree's & disappear. i'm trying to get an answer to this.
content.summary: It came out of no where without a sound. flew behind the tree's & was gone.
Again! next night! this time  another enity (same kind) movedd

content.detailedDescription: I was driving my vehicle on 67 north towards mapleview exit at approximately 6:45 am on 10/17/13.  the sun had not risen above the horizon yet and the sky was was getting light.  there are two mountains directly east of there about 50 miles east with a "valley" in between.  i saw a spot in the sky that was as bright as the sun but was only aspirin size in the sky.  i didn't know what it was but knew it wasn't a star or plane as stars and planes are not that bright.  it was like little pieces of the sun in the early morning sky.  as i sat at the stoplight, i watched the light in the sky slowly move in a northerly direction.  then all of a sudden a second and third light appeared.  one of the lights was elongated, almost like a shooting star but was kind of stationary and appeared like it was moving in a southerly direction.  the third light was a little bigger than the first and seemed like it was moving in a northerly direction.  as traffic started moving, i tried to keep watch.  the lights stayed for a few moments and then disappeared.  as i continued up the hill on 67n, i saw one of the lights had come back.  i then traveled too far to see anymore.  when i arrived at work in poway, i kept watch from a second story window, but the sun had risen and it was too bright.  i didn't see them again.  as i drove to work the following morning i looked for the lights but they were not there.
content.summary: Bright "sun-like" shapes in eastern san diego county early morning skies

content.detailedDescription: Myself & 2 other people were driving to our friends house when we seen a huge box shaped rectangular ufo hovering over the tree tops we pulled over & got out the car to look at it & when we got out it didnt make any noise at all & it was the size of a building just hovering there & it was close so close that i picked up a couple rocks & threw it at it & when they hit it sounded very solid we stood there a good 15 mins just looking at it the best way i could describe it was it looked like a cargo container but way larger than a normal cargo container it had 4 lights on it one in each corner a white light in top right corner a blue light in bottom right corner a blue light in top left corner a white light in bottom left corner they were very bright lights & they didnt flash or anything they just stayed on & it was in june a very hot day in the middle of the day between 3-5pm so it was very sunny outside broad daylight so i know somebody else had to see this object cause it was in a very busy part of town & it was huge i mean well over  100ft long & 20-30ft tall it was a rustic orange color on the sides & the bottom of it was black it had kind of a cargo container pattern on the sides how a cargo container goes in & out anyway we got back in the car against my will cause i wanted to wait around to see it leave but they convinced me to get back in the car so he could drive around to get a better look at it & we drove around the curve & lost sight of it in the trees & turned around & went back & it was gone
content.summary: A huge box shaped ufo

content.detailedDescription:
I was laying in bed looking up at the clouds out the window when i saw an object taking the usual flight path that planes take from bundaberg airport to lady elliott island.

normally there is engine noise audible within my bedroom as the plane goes over, this was silent- so i looked closer and it did not appear to be a plane nor a helicopter.

it was a metallic or silver sphere, as i watched it silently pass over it went inside a cloud (it's overcast today with sporadic smaller slow moving clouds)- the object did not appear to emerge from the cloud.

i ran downstairs with my binoculars and kept them fixed on the cloud for a few minutes- the object did not reappear.

the mufon submission form required me to choose a surface color but did not let me specify metallic/silver/chrome so i chose unknown- however it appeared to be a metallic/silver/chrome sphere.
content.summary: Chrome sphere with no sound

content.detailedDescription: I was heading north on i91 from new haven heading to hartford when a friend spotted the object first this object has appeared to him before in september and today as i'm reporting this he called me to tell me he seen it again on his way home. but what i witness was on highway between exit 14 and 15 i pulled over to get my camera to video what i was witnessing i was able to capture it but with a fixed focal length lens a 50mm i was also able to capture it 60fps at 720p  the footage i have does contain detailed camera log with exact time and date recorded.
content.summary: What i seen can only be described as similar to chinese floating lantern

content.detailedDescription: I was driving through my neighborhood and looked up. i saw two red lights and slowed down and drove through the neighborhood keeping an eye on them. i'd never seen lights in that portion of the sky and was a bit surprised and even lowered my window to take a better look and paused the car then continued to my house hoping for a better view. i thought they were unusually bright, even brighter than stars and for a moment i thought someone had put up a tower during the day while i was up at work. i thought it was super strange but as i drove through the neighborhood i noticed they were changing positions. when i got home which was less than a block i got out of my car and looked up and noticed they no longer were one above the other. they now were completely parallel to each other and were barely moving. there was no sound but they were still super bright and really big. there was no flickering and changing of colors which is what i've seen in airplanes and helicopters and no noise. this was a strong stationary red color that moved slowly and barely noticeably. after watching for between a minute to a minute and a half i noticed they were suddenly fading out like a flashlight with batteries dying and then they were gone. i felt as if they'd gone away from me. within a minute i noticed a jet crossing the sky at a really high altitude with blinking lights. we have the sarasota airport locally so it probably was a passenger jet. ironically, this helped me figure out the size as being probably two to three times bigger because the lights from the jet were tiny in comparison and blinking and much closer. the lights seemed to be right over the area that would be myakka park. i don't know what it was that i saw but i know this is nothing normal. i've lived here for at least 10 years and this was nothing like anything i've seen and i've seen all types of helicopters and planes cross over us.
content.summary: Two bright lights in sky that seemed to be above the area where myakka park would be

content.detailedDescription:
My son first pointed to the ufo. observed (3) blinking orange / white lights. lights appeared in a large triangle shape moving uniformly. observed lights for (20) seconds with my 7 yr old son. pulled out camera phone was only able to get (1) of the blinking lights to be viewable on the video.

1. where were you and what were you doing at the time?
   i was going to pickup pizza and my son pointed out the lights when i was exiting the garage. 

2. what made you first notice the object?
   my (7) year old son.

3. what did you think the object was when you first noticed it?
   to large to be a plane. thought right away it was a ufo.

4. describe the object and its actions and motions in detail.
   seen the ufo fly over houses a cross the street under cloud line. seen (3) blinking lights in a triangle design. lasted for 40 sec. then (2) of the lights disappeared leaving (1) blinking light.

5. describe your feelings, reactions and actions, during and after sighting the object.
   it was pretty cool. my son seen his 1st ufos also..I think it is my 1st one also.

6. how did you lose sight of the object?
  (2) of the (3) lights disappeared and then large trees abstracted the view. no noise was witnessed. 

video only contains (1) light blinking faintly..
content.summary: 3-light ufo

   i have the habit of looking up in the sky to see planes , stars and possible ufos.

then they moved very far from my window sight. it was 2 or possible 3 ufos.


from that time , i noticed some times some lights flying around , that does not apear to be plane , since there were no strobe light, the green red wing light.   i suspect they were man made , high tech space craft. but could be alien.

content.detailedDescription: I was on my deck at my house taking pictures of the sunset.  today, about 2 weeks later, i uploaded the pictures to my computer for editing.  i noticed a strange image on one of the photos.  i thought it was a small plane or maybe a dust particle on the camera lens but the shots i took immediately after and before did not have that image. i took the images consecutively, all within seconds of each other. the closer i zoomed into the other images i was able to see some unidentifiable object in each of the images, just not as clear as the first one i saw.  i will upload the images.  they have not been edited except for i think i cropped one of the images.  the image with the most evident object is #4404, you can see it under the moon, kind of.  the first shot (4403) only has the bright orb on the uppermost left hand side of the photo, looks like a star, but it is not int he other images.  in the rest of the images the object is unclear, more to the right but appears to be further away.
content.summary: Strange objects caught on photos

content.detailedDescription: I came outside shortly after 9pm, think there was a weird sound, quickly scanned around.  bright lights immediately caught my eye.  two very bright lights in line with each other, with just a little space between them.  they were somewhat low in the sky & close to the mountain ridge, about the height of an airplane flying quite low but moving very fast.  i would say the lights were bigger than an airplane's would be & there weren't any accompanying red or green lights visible.  i did not see any outline of the object itself, but feel as though the lights may've been more rectangular in shape rather than as star's appearance & my guess of the craft's shape would have to be saucer or disk-like. there was no sound as a helicopter or airplane would have, and it darted over the mountain southward very fast. i felt startled, excited, and a little silly.  also wondered if others had seen it.
content.summary: Two star-like bright lights on an non-visible craft moving much faster than airplane zipping over mountain top

content.detailedDescription: Around 510pm est on friday, october 18th, 2013, an object was located in the high sky in the east and was headed at what appeared to be due north. i was outside at work in the north of mcdonough, georgia. a coworker and i were pointing out a couple of the low flying planes to our small children. the children lost interest and i was about to, until a tiny speck caught my eye. i was mesmerized by it. a fleeting thought of an extremely high flying airplane flitted through my mind but was quickly dispelled. the object was between 60 and 75 degrees or so above the horizon. it was very small, as if someone had lost the tip of a ballpoint pen. it was white. i did not think it was shiny, rather it was more like an airplane's finish. it was perfectly roundish to my eye. there was a small gap- around the size of the object itself- between it and what seemed like a thin whitish-grey 'tail.' this tail was easily ten or so times longer than the object itself. curiously, this apparent tail followed the object and did not leave behind residue as an airplane trail does. the tail was blunt on the proximal end and possibly pointed on the distal end. the object was very high in the sky. it was up and close with the highest cirrus clouds. i have never seen anything so high up. it was flying in a very straight line. it was in the east and definitely headed northward. after two or so minutes i had my coworker come and see. she had to squint to see it and also at very first thought it to be a high airplane. but then she, too, saw that it was round and odd. our kids took no notice to it at all. and after about five to maybe ten minutes, i lost it in the clouds. please help me find out what this object was.
content.summary: Ballpoint pen tipped size, white, round, in the east headed north, very high near or above cirrus clouds.
